---

This month's Tokyo Indies was bustling with activity and a fresh batch of new games to show off. 

Zhixiang Zhu presented [Red Shift](https://globalgamejam.org/2018/games/red-shift), a game about communication between planets made for the Global Game Jam. You can play it for free at the link!

!embed https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=y45JrzXq-TI
<iframe width="612" height="344" src="https://www.youtube.com/embed/y45JrzXq-TI?feature=oembed" frameborder="0" allow="autoplay; encrypted-media" allowfullscreen></iframe>


[Azuma Goro](https://twitter.com/azumagoro) presented ReRotation, a card battle game inspired by Pokemon and Hearthstone. 

!embed https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=ss9WDxyVhOA
<iframe width="612" height="344" src="https://www.youtube.com/embed/ss9WDxyVhOA?feature=oembed" frameborder="0" allow="autoplay; encrypted-media" allowfullscreen></iframe>


[Qrostar](https://twitter.com/qrostar) presented [Counterhero](https://qrostar0.itch.io/counterhero1jp), a roguelike where you have the power to switch out numbers. Currently the first chapter is available only in Japanese, but an English translation is in progress.

!img counterhero.png

